688369de31f8,Who are the most important philosophers of the East?,"The most important Eastern philosophers include:
* Buddha - The founder of Buddhism, who was born in the 6th century BC, and who is believed to have attained enlightenment while meditating under a Bodhi tree. He preached the value of meditation and the importance of personal enlightenment and inner peace.
* Confucius - A Chinese philosopher, educator, and social reformer who lived from 551 to 479 BC. He is the founder of Confucianism, which advocates for harmony, social order, and respect for authority.
* Laozi - The author of the Tao Te Ching, the classic work of Taoist philosophy, which promotes the importance of accepting the flow of the universe and living in harmony with nature. He is believed to have lived around the 6th century BC.
* Mencius - A Chinese philosopher who lived from 372 to 289 BC. He was one of the most influential Confucianists, and he taught that human nature is innately good.
* Muhammad - The founder of Islam, who lived from 570 to 632. He is believed to have received revelations directly from God, which were recorded in the Quran.
* Zarathustra - The prophet of Zoroastrianism, who is believed to have lived around 1200 BC. He taught the importance of pursuing good deeds and living in accordance with God's will."
