e5c1a8d0a09a,give me example of spark sql to get event data from one kafka top and do some calculates and resink data to another kafka topic,"Sure, here's an example of a Spark SQL query that reads data from a Kafka topic, calculates some metrics, and writes the results to another Kafka topic:
```python
from pyspark.sql import SparkSession
from pyspark.sql.functions import avg, max, sum
from pyspark.sql.types import DoubleType

# Initialize Spark Session
spark = SparkSession.builder.appName(""Kafka-to-Kafka"").getOrCreate()

# Read data from Kafka topic
df = spark.readStream.format(""kafka"").option(""kafka.bootstrap.servers"", ""localhost:9092"").option(""subscribe"", ""my_topic"").load()

# Calculate average value of ""value"" field
df = df.withColumn(""avg_value"", avg(df[""value""]).over(""window""))

# Calculate maximum value of ""value"" field
df = df.withColumn(""max_value"", max(df[""value""]).over(""window""))

# Calculate sum of ""value"" field
df = df.withColumn(""sum_value"", sum(df[""value""]).over(""window""))

# Write results to another Kafka topic
df.writeStream.format(""kafka"").option(""kafka.bootstrap.servers"", ""localhost:9092"").option(""topic"", ""output_topic"").option(""checkpointLocation"", ""path/to/checkpoint"").outputMode(""append"").start(""my_kafka_output"")
```
This example reads data from a Kafka topic named ""my\_topic"", calculates the average, maximum, and sum of the ""value"" field over a window of 5 minutes, and writes the results to another Kafka topic named ""output\_topic"". The results are written in append mode, which means that new data will always be appended to the existing output topic. The checkpoint location is specified in case of a failure, allowing Spark to resume reading from the last checkpointed offset."
