3. Springer Nature: Springer Nature is a leading research and educational publisher that provides scientific and scholarly journals, books, and online resources. It was formed in 2015 through the merger of Springer Science+Business Media and Nature Publishing Group, and is headquartered in Berlin, Germany. It has a current revenue of around €2.3 billion.
4. Taylor & Francis Group: Taylor & Francis Group is a leading publisher of scholarly journals, books, eBooks, and online resources. It was founded in 1798 and is headquartered in Abingdon, Oxfordshire, UK. It has a current revenue of around £2.3 billion.
5. Sage Publishing: Sage Publishing is a leading international publisher of academic and professional books, journals, and online resources. It was founded in 1965 and is headquartered in Los Angeles, California, USA. It has a current revenue of around $560 million.
6. Palgrave Macmillan: Palgrave Macmillan is a global academic publisher that provides books, journals, and online resources in the humanities, social sciences, and business. It was founded in 2000 and is headquartered in New York, New York, USA. It has a current revenue of around $200 million.

Please note that the revenue figures listed above are approximate and may vary depending on the source. Additionally, there are many other"
