11143bb080dd,"Can you describe what a ""musky"" smell is?","A ""musky"" smell is a scent that is often described as earthy, rich, and somewhat heavy. It is usually associated with animalistic or sensual undertones, reminiscent of the natural odor produced by some mammals, particularly the musk deer. The term ""musk"" originally comes from the musk deer's secretion, which was used as a base note in perfumery. In general, musky smells can be warm, slightly sweet, and have a lingering quality, evoking a sense of deep, primal allure."
