5327d8259101,Who discovered the X-ray?,"The discovery of X-rays is credited to Wilhelm Conrad Roentgen, a German physicist who made this discovery accidentally while experimenting with cathode rays in 1895. He found that a screen coated with a fluorescent material produced a bright glow when exposed to invisible rays emanating from a cathode ray tube, even when the tube was covered to block all visible light. Roentgen called these previously unknown rays ""X-rays"", because their nature was unknown. His discovery revolutionized the fields of physics and medicine, and earned him the first Nobel Prize in Physics in 1901."
