860ab2493a84,Generate a new product design,"Introducing the new ""Smart Cart""! This innovative product combines the traditional grocery cart with cutting edge technology to make your shopping experience easy and efficient.

The Smart Cart is equipped with a touch screen panel on the handle, allowing you to scan and keep track of your items as you add them to the cart. The cart also has an in-built weighing scale that calculates the weight of the produce and bulk items for quick and accurate pricing. 

The touch screen interface also has a GPS feature which locates your position within the store and maps out the most efficient route to gather all of the items on your shopping list. Simply enter your shopping list into the system and the Smart Cart will do the rest!

Additionally, the Smart Cart includes a charging dock for your mobile phone, ensuring that you never run out of battery while shopping. It also features multiple hooks for reusable bags and a storage compartment for items such as coupons or wallets.

The Smart Cart has a sleek and modern design, made from durable materials to withstand the wear and tear of daily use. It also has a self-cleaning feature which ensures that the cart is always hygienic for the next shopper.

Make your shopping experience easy and efficient with the new Smart Cart!"
e76df0b31751,Do you know anything about stem-cell?,"I can say what I know, but I’m not a biologist, so please bear with me if there are parts that are inaccurate or if I don’t seem to fully understand the question.  
Stem cells are cells that have the ability to develop into specialized cells.  They are “master cells” which are able to make all the different kinds of cells in the body.  They’re found throughout our bodies, but are also used in medicine.  The stem cells that are used in medicine can be extracted from the patient’s body, or from an embryo.  The stem cells can be used to treat diseases, and in the process are changed into specific kinds of specialized cells.  For example, they can be used to treat leukemia or other kinds of cancer.  They can also be used to treat other diseases, like Parkinson’s and heart disease.  There are many different kinds of stem cells, but the most common ones used in medicine are called embryonic stem cells and adult stem cells.  Embryonic stem cells are derived from early-stage embryos, which have the ability to produce all of the different cells in the body.  Adult stem cells are adult cells that have the ability to produce specialized cells."
