2bdf51d67b61,Are diamonds really forever?,"Diamonds are not truly ""forever"" in a literal sense, as they can be damaged, destroyed, or lost. However, the phrase ""diamonds are forever"" comes from a marketing campaign by De Beers in 1947 to emphasize the durability and enduring value of diamonds. Diamonds are the hardest naturally occurring substance known, with a rating of 10 on the Mohs scale of mineral hardness. This durability, along with their rarity and beauty, contributes to the perception that they last forever."
