8804c784ccb0,Write a lisp program that computes fibonacci numbers,"Here is a Lisp program that computes Fibonacci numbers:

```lisp
(defun fib (n)
  (if (<= n 1) 
      n
    (+ (fib (- n 1)) 
       (fib (- n 2)))))

(print (fib 1)) ; 1
(print (fib 2)) ; 2 
(print (fib 3)) ; 3
(print (fib 4)) ; 5
(print (fib 5)) ; 8
(print (fib 6)) ; 13
```

This defines a recursive fib function that computes the nth Fibonacci number. It handles the base cases of n <= 1, and otherwise recursively calls fib(n-1) and fib(n-2) to compute the nth number."
