f265e1394cea,Explain why or whether it is reasonable to assume that the resampling distribution is similar enough to the sampling distribution for the non-parametric bootstrap.,"The non-parametric bootstrap is a procedure used to estimate the distribution of a statistic based on a small number of samples. The resampling distribution is the distribution of the estimated statistic based on the bootstrapped samples. If the resampling distribution is similar enough to the sampling distribution, then the non-parametric bootstrap is reasonable to use. This is because the non-parametric bootstrap makes use of the sampling distribution to estimate the distribution of the statistic, and thus the resampling distribution should be similar to the sampling distribution for the bootstrap to be reasonable."
