d41b23f3833e,what is a taxicab number?,"A taxicab number, also known as a Hardy-Ramanujan number, is a positive integer that can be expressed as the sum of two positive cubes in at least two different ways. These numbers are named after the famous mathematicians G. H. Hardy and Srinivasa Ramanujan, who discussed this concept in the early 20th century. 

The smallest taxicab number is 1729, which can be expressed as the sum of two cubes in two distinct ways: 1³ + 12³ and 9³ + 10³. Other taxicab numbers include 4104, 13832, and 20683. Taxicab numbers are interesting because they reveal unique properties and patterns within the realm of number theory."
