ef65412593db,How would someone working a full-time job break into a front-end developer position (preferably remote) making $50k/yr? Are there any specific projects that look good on a portfolio?,"To break into a front-end developer position, here are a few steps you can take:

1. Learn the necessary skills: Start by learning HTML, CSS, and JavaScript. There are many online resources available, such as Codecademy, Udemy, and Coursera. Practice building websites and web applications to gain experience.

2. Build a portfolio: Create a portfolio website to showcase your projects. Include a few examples of your work, such as websites, web applications, and mobile apps. Make sure your portfolio is well-organized and visually appealing.

3. Attend meetups and network: Attend local meetups and events to meet other developers and learn about new technologies. Networking can help you learn about job opportunities and connect with others in the industry.

4. Apply for remote positions: Look for remote front-end developer positions on job boards such as Indeed, Glassdoor, and LinkedIn. Make sure your resume and cover letter are tailored to the job description, highlighting your skills and experience.

As for specific projects that look good on a portfolio, here are a few ideas:

1. A responsive website: Create a website that looks great on desktop and mobile devices. Make sure it's optimized for speed and accessibility.

2. A web application: Build a web application that solves a real-world problem. This could be anything from a to-do list app to a weather app.

3. A mobile app: Create a mobile app using a framework like React Native or Flutter. Make sure the app is user-friendly and has a clean design.

Remember, the most important thing is to show off your skills and experience in a way that is clear and easy to understand. Good luck!"
f3dda2ad04d8,"With Keras, write a genetic algorithm that generates CNN models for RL","To write a genetic algorithm that generates CNN models for RL using Keras, we will first need to define the genetic algorithm's parameters, such as the population size, mutation rate, and number of generations. Next, we will define the function that evaluates the quality of a model and the function that mutates the model. We will also need to define the initialization of the population with a random set of model parameters.

