2e490f43a380,What's the difference between a cat and a lynx ?,"A lynx is a wild cat which is native to Europe and Asia. They are much larger than domestic cats and have a longer tail and a more slender build. Unlike domestic cats, lynxes do not have a separate house, but instead can live in forests or mountainous areas.

On the other hand, domestic cats are a popular pet and are often seen as friendly and loyal companions. They are typically small and have a shorter tail than lynxes. They also have a more diverse diet and are more adaptable than other cats.

Overall, the differences between a cat and a lynx are primarily physical and behavioral. Cats are generally more domesticated and are often used as pets, while lynxes are wild animals and are not commonly kept as pets."
