62c371c70671,write me a js code that can scrape a website through the browsers element inspector,"There are different ways to scrape data from a website using JavaScript. One way is to use the Console panel of the browser’s developer tools to write JavaScript code that can access the HTML elements of the webpage. Another way is to use a JavaScript library such as Puppeteer or Cheerio that can automate browser actions and manipulate DOM elements.

Here is an example of a simple JS code that can scrape the title and author of each quote from https://quotes.toscrape.com/ using the Console panel:

```
// Select all div elements with class ""quote""
let quotes = document.querySelectorAll(""div.quote"");

// Loop through each quote element
for (let quote of quotes) {
  // Get the text content of the span element with class ""text""
  let text = quote.querySelector(""span.text"").textContent;
  // Get the text content of the small element with class ""author""
  let author = quote.querySelector(""small.author"").textContent;
  // Print the text and author
  console.log(text + "" - "" + author);
}
```"
