ae18a3a0ec66,i'd like to use LDAP authentication in my spring-boot application . when an API gets hit i'd like to override the authentication token and pass it to LDAP integration to authenticate the user and get the user roles.,"To achieve this, you can follow these steps:

Step 1: Configure LDAP integration in your Spring Boot application

First, you need to create an LDAP server and configure it to authenticate users. You can use the `ldapAuth` JAR or the `LdapNamingStore` class provided by the `org.springframework.ldap` module.

Here is an example of how to configure LDAP integration in a Spring Boot application:
```java
@Configuration
@EnableLdap
public class LdapConfig extends LdapAuthorizationServerConfigurerAdapter {

    @Override
    public void configure(LdapContext ctx) throws NamingException {
        // Configure the LDAP server
        ctx.addComponent(""ldap-context"", new LdapContext(ctx.getAuthentication()));
        ctx.addComponent(""ldap-service"", new LdapService(ctx.getAuthentication()));
        ctx.addComponent(""ldap-login-config"", new LdapLoginConfig());

        // Configure the authentication provider
        ctx.authenticationProvider(new UsernamePasswordAuthenticationProvider(ctx.getAuthentication()));
    }

    @Override
    public void configure(AuthenticationManagerBuilder auth) throws UsernameNotFoundException {
        // Configure the LDAP authentication provider
        auth.authenticationProvider(ctx.getAuthentication());
    }

    @Override
    public void configure(AuthorizationServerEndpointsConfigurer endpoints) throws UsernameNotFoundException {
        // Configure the LDAP authentication provider
        endpoints.authenticationProvider(ctx.getAuthentication());
    }
}
```

