William Wordsworth","William Wordsworth (1770-1850) was an English Romantic poet known for helping to launch the Romantic Age in English literature with the joint publication of ""Lyrical Ballads"" with Samuel Taylor Coleridge. One of his most famous works is ""The Prelude"", an autobiographical poem that retraces the poet’s own spiritual development and experiences from childhood. Additionally, his poem ""I Wandered Lonely as a Cloud"" is a famous work that vividly describes the beauty of nature and its ability to evoke joy and happiness in the observer."
