737ce25016fd,Who invented the idea of black friday shopping?,"According to Wikipedia, the original idea of a Black Friday was by the owner of a Philadelphia department store in the early 1920’s.  He sought to give his shop a boost after the difficult post-war years, and during a hectic Christmas season he successfully marketed a huge sale that drew throngs of shoppers to his store.  The owner made more profit than he’d expected, and the term “Black Friday” quickly came to mean the day after Thanksgiving, or the day after a big sale event."
