5f14c2e55556,What's the real story of the Brothers Grimm?,"The Brothers Grimm were German linguists and folklorists who were born in the early 19th century. Their real names were Wilhelm and Jakob Grimm. They are best known for collecting and publishing folk tales and fairy tales, which they collected from peasants and other members of the working class. These tales, which included classics such as ""Cinderella,"" ""Snow White,"" and ""Rapunzel,"" were originally told orally and had been passed down through generations. The Grimm brothers also studied and wrote about language, and they are credited with developing the first German dictionary of the modern language. They were also involved in the study of law and philology. They died in the late 19th century, but their work continues to be popular and influential to this day."
