373736c9d369,"Write a node.js program to print out ""Hello World"" in the console.","Here is a simple Node.js program to print out ""Hello World"" in the console:

```javascript
// Load the http module to create an http server.
const http = require('http');

// Configure our HTTP server to respond with Hello World to all requests.
const server = http.createServer((req, res) => {
    res.writeHead(200, {""Content-Type"": ""text/plain""});
    res.end(""Hello World\n"");
});

// Listen on port 8000, IP defaults to 127.0.0.1
server.listen(8000);

// Put a friendly message on the terminal
console.log(""Server running at http://127.0.0.1:8000/"");
```

To run this program, save it to a file with a `.js` extension, such as `hello_world.js`. Then, open your command-line interface, navigate to the directory where you saved the file, and run `node hello_world.js`. You should see the message ""Server running at http://127.0.0.1:8000/"" printed to the console, and if you open a web browser and navigate to `http://127.0.0.1:8000`, you should see the message ""Hello World""."
23227351a5e7,Compare and contrast theologies of Calvinism and Lutheranism.,"Calvinism and Lutheranism are two of the most prominent branches of Protestant theology that emerged in the 16th century during the Reformation. They share many similarities, including the belief in salvation through faith alone, the priesthood of all believers, and the authority of the Bible. However, there are also some significant differences between the two.

One major difference is their view on predestination. Calvinists, following the teachings of John Calvin, believe in the doctrine of double predestination, which states that God has already determined who will be saved and who will be damned, and that nothing an individual can do can change their predestined fate. Lutherans, on the other hand, following the teachings of Martin Luther, reject this idea, and instead believe that human beings have free will and can choose to accept or reject the grace of God.

Another difference between Calvinism and Lutheranism is their understanding of the presence of Christ in the Eucharist. Lutherans believe in the doctrine of the Real Presence, which states that Christ is truly present in the bread and wine of the Eucharist. Calvinists, on the other hand, believe in a spiritual presence, where Christ is present, but not in a physical sense.

A third difference between the two is the way they view the role of the church and its relationship to the state. Calvinists believe in a theocracy, where the church has a great deal of influence over the government and society. In contrast, Lutherans advocate for a separation of church and state, where the church has no official influence over the government.

In summary, while Calvinism and Lutheranism share many basic tenets of Protestantism, there are also some significant differences between the two in terms of their views on predestination, the Eucharist, and the relationship between church and state."
43b5830a16af,Can you explain where the money comes from for these big powerball jackpots?,"I can try to explain the mechanics of how lotteries and other contests work.  The specific source of the money varies by state, but essentially each lottery pays a percentage of the sales proceeds back to the state in the form of tax revenue."
