a4ea7f1314d8,What is the significance of pi?,"Pi (π) is a mathematical constant that represents the ratio of the circumference of a circle to its diameter. It is a non-repeating, non-terminating decimal that starts with 3.14159 and goes on infinitely. Pi has many applications in mathematics, physics, engineering, and technology, and is used to calculate the area and volume of circles, spheres, and cylinders. It is also used in trigonometry, calculus, and other branches of mathematics. Pi has fascinated mathematicians for centuries and has been studied and calculated to millions of decimal places."
