7ef37a1cf456,Is a dashcam worth the cost?,"That’s a really great question!  Dashcams are typically used to record accidents whenever a vehicle is damaged, and they can also be useful for prosecuting perpetrators if the driver was responsible for a vehicle-related crime.  That said, if you don’t have a need for a dashcam, then the additional cost for one probably isn’t worth it -- it’s often relatively expensive, and it doesn’t always protect people from insurance claims or accusations of criminal wrongdoing.  Really, the biggest reason to get a dashcam is to ensure that the driver has a truly accurate account of what happened during and leading up to an accident, no matter who was at fault for it."
