d1221a6545b4,What is the maximum number of steps in a Fibonacci sequence?,"A Fibonacci sequence is a sequence of numbers in which each number is the sum of the two numbers preceding it, starting with 0 and 1. Theoretically, there is no maximum number of steps in a Fibonacci sequence, as the sequence can continue indefinitely. Each additional number in the sequence can be calculated by adding the previous two numbers, so the sequence can continue as long as you would like to compute it."
