02dcbfa1ed84,Is heating using microwave same as heating with gas?,"Heating with a microwave is not the same as heating with gas. In general, microwaves heat food more quickly than gas, but the heat produced is not as even as when using gas. Additionally, microwaves may produce a more concentrated heat that can cause some food items to become overcooked in certain areas while remaining undercooked in other areas. Gas, on the other hand, produces a more even heat and is better suited for cooking items that require more precise heat control."
e6d3be25272b,How do solar systems form?,"Solar systems form when a large cloud of dust and gas called a molecular cloud collapses under its own gravity. As it collapses, it begins to form a dense core called a protostar. Over time, the core heats up and compresses, eventually becoming a full-fledged star. The leftover dust and gas around the star then forms a planetary system."
