fdd34ae837ad,What should I do to stay safe during a tornado warning?,"Since tornadoes are powerful, violent storms with strong winds, and can sometimes form rapidly, it’s best to keep a close eye on the weather and ensure your house is built securely against these hazards.  There are a few things you can do to reduce your risk of injury.  The first is to locate your storm shelter, and make sure you know how to get there in case a tornado approaches.  Second, if your home is surrounded by trees, you’ll want to make sure they are well-trimmed so they can’t fall onto your house and potentially cause injury.  Third, keep a close eye on the sky, and only open windows or step out of the house for essential tasks.  If you have a basement, make sure it is not flooded with water, and that you know the safest and most accessible place to seek shelter in the house.  Finally, if your family owns a video baby monitor or pet monitor, consider installing"
