fc37de12ae59,Solve the following math equation: 8x + 9y = 180,"The equation 8x + 9y = 180 has infinitely many solutions because this is a linear equation with two variables: x and y. It describes a line in the coordinate plane, and all points that lie on that line are the solutions of the equation. In other words, you can find many different pairs (x, y) that satisfy this equation. 

However, if you want to express y in terms of x, you can do the following steps:

8x + 9y = 180
9y = 180 - 8x
y = (180 - 8x) / 9

So, for any value of x that you choose, you can find a corresponding value of y that makes the equation true. For example, if x = 10, then y = (180 - 8 * 10) / 9 = 12."
