d91f4243e036,What is an appendicitis?,"Appendicitis is an infection of the appendix, an organ in the abdomen which has the role of regulating the contents of the intestines. The appendix is usually described as a ""blind pouch"" or a ""pocket"", as it is made up of smooth muscle and does not contain any nerves or blood vessels. The appendix is a temporary structure, and, in healthy people, usually degenerates and disappears during infancy. It is located near the junction of the large and small intestines. Infection is the result of microorganisms entering the body via the large intestine. After entering the abdomen, the microorganisms can grow in the relatively anaerobic environment, and be transported via the blood stream to the site of infection."
