1f5e6a6809b6,what is King Charles's relationship between diana and Camilla,"King Charles's relationship with Diana and Camilla is a complex and controversial topic.

At the time of his marriage to Diana, Prince Charles was already having an extramarital affair with Camilla Parker Bowles. The relationship continued even after Diana's death in 1997, and Charles and Camilla eventually married in 2005.

Diana's relationship with Charles was tumultuous and marked by infidelity on both sides. Diana famously accused Charles of having affairs with Camilla and other women, and there were reports of emotional and physical abuse in their marriage.

Camilla was often portrayed as a ""other woman"" in the media and was widely criticized for her role in the breakdown of Charles and Diana's marriage. However, she has since become a beloved member of the royal family and has worked to improve her public image.

The relationship between Charles and Diana was marked by highs and lows, and it was not always smooth sailing for the couple. Despite this, Diana was and will always be remembered for her humanitarian work and her role as a mother to her two sons."
6d3b2b3d6299,write t-sql code to find the last business day of the month,"To find the last business day of the month in T-SQL, you can use the following code:
```
vbnetUSE AdventureWorks2017
GO
DECLARE @dt DATETIME
DECLARE @dtEndOfMonth DATETIME
SET @dt = DATEADD(month, DATEDIFF(month, 0, GETDATE()), 0)
SET @dtEndOfMonth = DATEADD(day, -1, DATEADD(month, 1, @dt))
IF DATEPART(dw, @dtEndOfMonth) = 1
BEGIN
    SET @dt = DATEADD(day, 1, @dtEndOfMonth)
END
SELECT @dt
```
This code uses the `DATEPART` function to extract the day of the month from the `@dt` variable and then checks if the day of month is 1. If it is, the code then subtracts one day using the `DATEADD` function and the `DATEPART` function to get the last business day of the month. If the day of month is not 1, the code increments the day of the month by 1 and repeats the process until the day of month is 1. The code then assigns the last business day of the month to the `@dtEndOfMonth` variable."
dd7b11b43791,"Write a long story using the following details:
An Amazon called Lilly is really proud of her strength.
She decides to challenge She Hulk to see who is stronger.
She Hulk is impressed by Lilly. They both compare height before the fight and Lilly ends up being taller than She Hulk.
They both grab their hands and push each other to see who is the strongest.
At the beginning they're matched, but after a while She Hulk ends up exhausted and sweating a lot.
She Hulk asks for a recess to recover some energy.
Lilly is proud after realizing she doesn't need to rest, but she gives She Hulk time.","Lilly was an Amazon warrior, known for her incredible strength. She was smaller in stature than some of her fellow Amazons, but she made up for it with her fierce determination and unbreakable spirit.

One day, Lilly decided to challenge She Hulk to a strength test. She Hulk was an imposing figure, even among the super-powered heroes of the Marvel universe. She was enormous, with bulging muscles and incredible strength.

Lilly was a bit nervous as she approached She Hulk, but she was also determined to prove herself. She Hulk seemed to sense Lilly's nerves, and she smiled at the smaller Amazon.

""Hey there, little one,"" She Hulk said. ""You're really brave to challenge me like this. I'm impressed.""

Lilly stood up a little straighter, suddenly feeling a little more confident. She and She Hulk compared height, and to Lilly's surprise, she discovered that she was actually taller than the Hulk's cousin.

""Well, let's see what you've got,"" She Hulk said, grinning.

Lilly and She Hulk grabbed each other's hands and pushed, trying to outdo the other. At first, they were evenly matched, but as the minutes ticked by, it became clear that She Hulk was starting to tire.

""Hey, Lilly,"" She Hulk said, panting. ""I'm starting to feel a little tired. Could we take a break?""

Lilly was surprised by She Hulk's request. She had never thought of herself as being stronger than the Hulk's cousin, but maybe she was.

""Sure,"" Lilly said, feeling a little more confident. ""But I can keep going if you want.""

She Hulk shook her head, wiping sweat from her forehead. ""No, no. I don't want to hold you back. You go ahead and show me what you've got.""

And so Lilly did. She pushed with all her might, and She Hulk slowly started to tire. It wasn't long before She Hulk was panting and sweating, her muscles trembling with the effort.

""Okay"
