5. A plate, to serve the sandwich on.

Optional ingredients that you can add to enhance the taste of the sandwich include honey, bananas, or any other fruit of your choice."
68e7f4ec758e,How do I calm a baby who has had a nightmare?,"It depends on whether the baby is asleep or awake, but the best way to approach it is to avoid upsetting the baby further.  Generally it’s good to remain very calm and keep your voice low and soothing.  You can also hold the baby close, and try to figure out if the baby is distressed by something in particular, or just having a bad dream in general.  If the baby is awake, but having a nightmare, it’s good to ask the baby if they can describe the nightmare, and try to figure out the source of the distress.  In a calm environment with a caring person, the baby’s brain will be capable of processing the bad experience, so you can help calm the baby and eventually help them move on from the bad experience, or see if you can find a way to help the baby understand what was happening."
