7fee0b249b22,"What should I say if someone tells me ""Go back to your country?""","It sounds like what they’re doing is asking you to re-evaluate your allegiance and your identity.  This is actually a pretty common way of trying to force an emotional response in people.  People who try to make you feel guilty are trying to put you in a position where it’s really uncomfortable for you to express your opinions.  Your strategy can be to take a deep breath and take a step back, and think about your response.  This isn’t a personal attack.  When people attack you personally, they’re trying to get you to back down, but when they ask you to re-evaluate your identity, they’re trying to get you to question your own commitment to your opinion.  If you’re committed to what you’re saying, it shouldn’t really matter what they say, right?  What do you think?"
