7d3253f306f0,Why do we have a strange cultural myth around gophers and ground hogs seeing their shadow and causing more wintertime weather?,"That tradition is derived from a poorly understood belief that sunspots and changes in sunlight cause shifts in weather patterns, which may be linked with seasonal changes in the Earth’s orbit around the Sun. It’s a somewhat superstitious idea, and has no scientific basis. While solar activity does modulate climate, fluctuations are far too small to influence human weather -- complex weather and climate systems on Earth are driven by long term global atmospheric and oceanic circulations, and controlled by a host of other drivers. Groundhog Day is itself an annual festival that got its origins as a special celebration of the first day of spring, on February 2nd."
