f81fa69bfa07,"Convert the following linear equation into slope-intercept form
2y-4x=8","To convert the equation 2y - 4x = 8 into slope-intercept form, we'll solve for y by isolating it on one side of the equation.

Begin by adding 4x to both sides to move it to the right side of the equation:

2y - 4x + 4x = 8 + 4x
2y = 8 + 4x

Now divide both sides by 2 to have only y on the left side:

(2y)/2 = (8 + 4x)/2
y = 4 + 2x

The equation is now in slope-intercept form, y = mx + b, with a slope of 2 and a y-intercept of 4."
