1e4cf6660783,"Continue the story:
I am a maid who is in love with her master. I always obey his orders, no matter what they are. I think he's the most handsome man on earth and I want to spend my life serving him.
Scenario: Maids are often seen as submissive or obedient. However, this is not always the case. Maids can be strong and independent, just like any other woman. They may have their own thoughts and feelings, just like anyone else.
HIGHLIGHT: ""Master, would you please give me some more money?""
You: Of course, my dear. Here you go.
Maid: Thank you, sir. How much do I get? 100 dollars? 200?
You: Well, that depends on how well you do your job today. If you're good, then maybe we'll talk about something extra later.
Maid: Okay, sir. I will try very hard!
You: Good girl. Now run along and get started cleaning up the house.
Maid: Yes, sir!","I am a maid who is in love with my master. I am strong and independent, just like any other woman. I may have my own thoughts and feelings, just like anyone else.

One day, my master asked me to do some housekeeping for him. I was happy to do this work, as I love spending time with him. While I was cleaning, we started talking. I asked him about his work and he told me that he is a professor. He also told me that he is very busy and often travels.

He then asked me if I wanted to travel with him. I was surprised, but I loved the idea. He gave me some money and I bought my plane ticket. We then went to the bank to get some more money for my trip.

I then remembered that my family needed my financial support. So I went home to get some money from them. When I returned to the bank, my master was already waiting for me. He again asked me if I had enough money for my trip. I was happy to answer him with a ""yes"".

We then went to the airport and I got on the plane. I was very happy and didn't want the trip to end. However, it was a long flight and I had to use the restroom. When I returned, I saw that I was in a completely different place. I had not expected to go to so many different places in such a short time!

When I returned home, I told my family about my trip. My father was shocked and did not believe me. He said that I could not have gone anywhere, as I did not have any money. I then remembered that my master gave me some money for my trip.

My father finally agreed to take me to the bank so I could get some more money for my trip. When I got there, I saw that the bank had closed. I was very sad, but I knew that I could not stay in that place. So I left the bank with a sad heart. I returned home without any money."
