2356a651dd3b,"Construct a function to classify words into nouns, verbs, and adjectives.","One way to classify words into their part of speech is to use natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as Parts of Speech (POS) tagging. Here, I will construct a function using Python's Natural Language Toolkit (NLTK) library that classifies words into nouns, verbs, and adjectives:

```python

import nltk
from nltk.corpus import wordnet

nltk.download('averaged_perceptron_tagger')
nltk.download('wordnet')

def classify_words(word):
    # use the nltk library for POS tagging
    part_of_speech = nltk.pos_tag([word])[0][1]
    
    # define the POS tags that represent nouns, verbs, and adjectives
    noun_tags = [""NN"", ""NNS"", ""NNP"", ""NNPS""]
    verb_tags = [""VB"", ""VBD"", ""VBG"", ""VBN"", ""VBP"", ""VBZ""]
    adjective_tags = [""JJ"", ""JJR"", ""JJS""]
    
    # check if the POS tag of the given word matches any of the defined tags
    if part_of_speech in noun_tags:
        return ""Noun""
    elif part_of_speech in verb_tags:
        return ""Verb""
    elif part_of_speech in adjective_tags:
        return ""Adjective""
    else:
        return ""Other""

```
To test this function, let's try classifying different words:

```python
# Testing the classify_words function
print(classify_words('cat'))          # expected result: Noun
print(classify_words('jump'))         # expected result: Verb
print(classify_words('happy'))        # expected result: Adjective
print(classify_words('quickly'))      # expected result: Adverb
```
 
Note that this example solution can correctly identify nouns, verbs, and adjectives, but would not be able to classify other parts of speech such as adverbs correctly as the function is designed to only return one of ""Noun"", ""Verb"", ""Adjective"", or ""Other""."
99784656aa40,"I have a github repo fork, how can I add it to my origin with `git remote add` ?","To add your forked repository as a remote, you can use the `git remote add` command. The syntax for this command is `git remote add <name> <url>`. So, in your case, you would use `git remote add origin <url-of-your-forked-repo>`. This will add your forked repository as a remote to your local repository."
