62b169cf1920,Is hermeticism a philosophical or spiritual concept? And what would define the difference between the concepts?,"Hermeticism is a philosophical and spiritual concept that originated in the Hellenistic period of ancient Greece and Egypt. It is based on the teachings and writings attributed to the mythical figure Hermes Trismegistus, who was believed to be a combination of the Greek god Hermes and the Egyptian god Thoth.

Hermeticism encompasses both philosophical and spiritual ideas, including the belief in the unity of all things, the idea that the universe is an emanation of the divine, and the pursuit of spiritual transformation and enlightenment. It also includes practices such as alchemy, astrology, and the use of symbolic language and imagery to convey spiritual concepts.

The difference between philosophical and spiritual concepts is often a matter of emphasis and focus. Philosophical concepts tend to be more analytical and intellectual in nature, focused on abstract ideas and logical reasoning. Spiritual concepts, on the other hand, tend to be more experiential and focused on personal transformation and transcendence.

In the case of hermeticism, the philosophical aspects of the tradition might focus on ideas such as the nature of reality, the relationship between the individual and the cosmos, and the role of reason and intuition in understanding the world. The spiritual aspects might focus on practices such as meditation, ritual, and spiritual alchemy, aimed at achieving a deeper understanding of the self and the universe, and the attainment of spiritual enlightenment."
d25d1597ea70,How can I take good care of my bones?,"Excellent question!  This is a very important topic to understand, particularly as we age.  Here are a few key points to keep in mind: 

-Adequate calcium and vitamin D intake is extremely important for bone health.  Leafy green vegetables like kale are an excellent source of calcium, and a healthy diet should also include limited saturated fats, large quantities of fruits and vegetables, and lots of protein and dietary fiber.  Vitamin D is found in fortified foods and in fatty fish like salmon and mackerel.  In addition to a healthy diet, appropriate weight-bearing exercise and regular physical activity are also essential for bone health. 

-Avoiding excessive alcohol consumption, tobacco use, and illicit drug use is also important for bone health.  Excessive alcohol use can lead to osteoporosis or other bone problems, and tobacco use has been shown to reduce bone density.  Illicit drug use including marijuana and cocaine can also lead to serious bone health problems. 

-Avoiding excessive sunlight exposure can help prevent vitamin D deficiency, which can also lead to osteoporosis.  

-Maintaining a healthy body weight and staying active throughout life are essential for avoiding osteop"
d7cbb4e44c1b,When was Australia founded as a country?,"That is a tricky question! I’m not actually sure if I can give a definite answer. One reason is that while Australia has had a “government” for hundreds of years, there has been a sense of a united Australian “country” for less than two centuries. Many people think of Australia as having been founded in 1788, when the First Fleet arrived at Botany Bay, but I don’t know if you would call it a “country” back then. A more recent sense of a unified Australia is of course marked by the Federation in 1901. There has also been a sense of Australian identity and unity since World War II, but I’m not sure how to capture that in terms of a specific founding. I hope that helps to explain my uncertainty."
