5a726ba905bf,What architectural style is the Eiffel Tower?,"The Eiffel Tower, built in 1889 in Paris, France, is an iron lattice tower designed in the distinct architectural style of structural expressionism. This style emphasizes the expression of a building's structural system or construction materials in its architectural design. The tower was designed by Gustave Eiffel, an engineer, and his collaborators Maurice Koechlin and Émile Nouguier, who showcased the potential of the metal for constructions. At the time of its construction, it was considered a pure example of technical mastery in Iron design, and it was considered avant-garde."
