47252c7d8e2d,Why is traffic so bad in LA compared to other US cities?,"There are several reasons why traffic is more congested in Los Angeles compared to other US cities. One of the main reasons is the high population density in the city, which makes it difficult to build new roads and highways. Additionally, Los Angeles is located in a basin surrounded by mountains, which makes it harder for cars to bypass traffic.
Another reason is the city's dependence on private automobiles, which is more prevalent in Los Angeles than in other cities. The city's culture and lifestyle also encourage driving, which further exacerbates traffic congestion.
Finally, the city's aging infrastructure and lack of investment in maintaining roads and highways also contribute to traffic congestion.
Overall, traffic congestion in Los Angeles is a complex issue that is influenced by a variety of factors, including population density, infrastructure, and urban design."
