c7194bdba19e,What are some healthy snacks my child can take for recess that are low fat but filled with protein?,"Hmm, that’s a tricky issue and there are many different perspectives on what constitutes a healthy snack, especially for young children.  Overall I think it is important to emphasize consumption of fruits and vegetables, which are naturally high in micronutrients, antioxidants, fiber, and other valuable nutrients, yet relatively low in calories and fat.  It is also important to emphasize whole grains and legumes, which again are nutritious and provide a more complete nutritional profile than simple carbohydrates.  Here are some specific healthy snack suggestions that are low in fat but rich in protein:

-   A bowl of fruit and yogurt (especially low-fat plain yogurt)
-   Hummus and whole-wheat pita chips
-   Whole-wheat pretzels and cheese sticks
-   Whole-wheat bagels with nut butter
-   Homemade fruit and nut bars
-   Whole-wheat or sprouted-grain tortilla wraps with hummus or other veggie fillings
-   Homemade trail mix with nuts, dried fruit, and nut butters
-   Peanut butter and banana sandwiches
-   Fruit and nut trail mix
-   Brown rice cakes and nut butter"
