1d07010678a5,Is justified true belief knowledge?,"Justified true belief is one of the most commonly held definitions of knowledge. It states that knowledge is formed when a belief is both justified and true. In order for a belief to be justified, it must be based on evidence or a logical argument. In order for a belief to be true, it must be accurate and based on reality. This definition of knowledge is widely accepted in the philosophy and academic communities."
