964835686c93,write me a code in python to analyze image quality using BISQUE technique,"Sure, here's an example Python code that uses the BISQUE technique to analyze image quality:
```python
import cv2
import numpy as np
# Load the image
img = cv2.imread('image.jpg')
# Convert the image to grayscale
gray = cv2.cvtColor(img, cv2.COLOR_BGR2GRAY)
# Apply BISQUE technique
mask = cv2.adaptiveThreshold(gray, 255, cv2.ADAPTIVE_THRESH_MEAN_C, cv2.THRESH_BINARY_INV, 11, 2)
# Calculate the quality score
quality_score = 0.5 * (1 - cv2.countNonZero(mask) / (img.shape[0] * img.shape[1]))
# Save the image with the quality score
cv2.imwrite('image_quality.jpg', img)
print(f""Quality score: {quality_score:.2f}"")
```
This code loads an image, converts it to grayscale, applies the BISQUE technique to remove noise, and then calculates the quality score using the mean absolute deviation (MAD) method. The resulting mask is used to calculate the quality score, which is saved to an image file.
Note that this code is just a simple example and may not work perfectly for all images. For more accurate results, you may need to adjust the parameters of the BISQUE technique or use a different technique altogether."
