e16d64bd67b3,Explain the equivalence between compression and intelligence.,"Compression can be thought of as a form of intelligence as it involves taking data and reducing its size without losing any of its important information. Just like a smart person can quickly understand the gist of a long email, a smart compression algorithm can quickly understand the essence of a large file. It is able to identify the most significant data points and encode them in a way that reduces the file size without compromising its quality. This is similar to how a smart person can efficiently use their time and energy to solve problems, while a smart compression algorithm can efficiently use its resources to reduce the size of data files."
2acbb7604fc6,How do you heal a tongue ulcer?,"An ulcer or “ulceration” of the tongue is an open sore on the surface of the tongue. The most frequent causes of tongue ulcers are viral infections like herpes simplex (types 1 and 2), bacteria or bacterial toxins, and various forms of injury and trauma. Natural healing of tongue ulcers occurs by increasing blood flow to the affected area, promoting faster removal of dead and infected tissue, and stimulating production of additional connective tissue to aid in healing. Increasing intake of water and other fluids will also aid in recovery, as dehydration and lowered blood volume makes healing more difficult. Treatment of ulcers is generally based on removing causes of the ulcer and promoting healing. Analgesics (painkillers) can help with pain and discomfort during the healing process. Antiseptic mouthwashes can help promote healing and prevent secondary infection. Antiviral medical treatments and antibiotic medications may also be necessary to clear underlying infections. If herpes simplex is the cause, antiviral medications can reduce the severity and speed up the healing of the tongue ulcer. Strong pronunciations and extended use of the tongue that put strain on the affected area should be avoided until the ulcer has healed, to prevent re-injury and prolonging the healing process"
