acf619a133ae,Write an example of odoo module. It is important to have the file structure and the most important files,"An example of an Odoo module can be found in the `odoo-8.0` repository on Github. I have cloned the repository locally and inspected the `stock` module, which is a basic inventory management system.

The structure of the `stock` module is as follows:

```
odoo-8.0/odoo/modules/stock/
├── __init__.py
├── __openerp__.py
├── static/src/css/stock_style.css
├── templates/
│   ├── account.xml
│   ├── stock_move_lines.xml
│   ├── stock.xml
│   └── stock_rules.xml
├── views/
│   ├── account.xml
│   ├── stock_move_lines.xml
│   └── stock.xml
├── views/stock_forms.xml
├── views/stock_views.xml
└── xml/
    └── manifest.xml
```

The most important files in the `stock` module are:

- `stock/__init__.py`: This file defines the module name, the version, and the dependencies. It also imports the models and views defined in other files.
- `stock/views/stock_forms.xml`: This file defines the forms for the `stock` module.
- `stock/views/stock_views.xml`: This file defines the views for the `stock` module.
- `stock/stock.xml`: This file defines the menu structure for the `stock` module.
- `stock/stock_rules.xml`: This file defines the rules for the stock movement.
- `stock/stock.py`: This file defines the models for the `stock` module.

This is just an example of a basic module. A real-world Odoo module can be much more complex and may have many more files."
