                writer = csv.writer(csvfile)
                writer.writerow([TIMESTEPS*iters, mean_reward, std_reward]) ","Here is a refactored version:

```python
best_reward_threshold = 0.7 * best_reward 

if mean_reward > best_reward_threshold:
    model.save(f""{models_dir}/{TIMESTEPS*iters}"")
    with open(f""{models_dir}/best_rewards.csv"", 'a', newline='') as csvfile:
        writer = csv.writer(csvfile)
        writer.writerow([TIMESTEPS*iters, mean_reward, std_reward])
```

I extracted the best_reward_threshold variable to avoid the duplication. And restructured the logic to check just one condition instead of checking two separate conditions for best_reward > 0 and best_reward <= 0."
