e909703183fb,Complete the analogy. Chess is to 64 as tic-tac-toe is to blank.,"Chess is to 64 as tic-tac-toe is to 9. 

Chess is a board game played on a checkered board with 64 squares arranged in an eight-by-eight grid. Each player begins the game with 16 pieces: 8 pawns, 2 rooks, 2 knights, 2 bishops, 1 queen, and 1 king. The objective of the game is to checkmate the opponent's king, whereby the king is in a position to be captured (in ""check"") and there is no way to remove it from check.

Tic-tac-toe is a board game for two players, played on a 3×3 grid. The game is played by placing Xs and Os in the grid, one per turn. The first player to get three of their marks in a row (horizontally, vertically, or diagonally) wins the game.

The number of squares on the board is an important factor in both games. In chess, the larger board allows for more complex strategies and tactics. In tic-tac-toe, the smaller board makes the game more predictable and easier to solve."
