11cba9f7115c,"Is the statement correct?
A neutron is a stable subatomic particle.","No, the statement is not entirely correct. While it is true that a neutron is a subatomic particle, it is not always stable. A free neutron (one not within an atomic nucleus) has a half-life of approximately 10 minutes and will undergo beta decay to transform into a proton, an electron, and an antineutrino. Within an atomic nucleus, a neutron can be stable and contribute to the stability of the nucleus."
